Detailed Description

Obsolete - all sound classes from AddOns/MultiMedia have been replaced by a new audio concept. Use the AudioDeviceManager instead for playing sounds.

virtual void AbstractIMelodyParser::Parse (  BinData *  data,
IMelodyData &  parsed_data
)  [pure virtual]
 

Parses the IMelody given in data into parsed_data. The memory for parsed_data.m_tone_data.tones is allocated. parsed_data.m_tone_data.nof_tones is set to the maximum numbers of SingleTones which can be stored. This is the only valid value in parsed_data.
Note: The global volume value as defined in IMelody spec. must be the first SingleTones in parsed_data.m_tone_data.nof_tones if it is set.
If the given data cannot be parsed, parsed_data.m_tone_data.nof_tones should be set to 0.
